<!-- #breadcrumbs -->
<section id="post-content"><h1>Leaving a Legacy</h1>
<h3>Remembering New College in your Will</h3>
<p>Legacies have played, and continue to play, a major part in the history of New College. As a charitable institution, bequests to the College are free of Inheritance Tax. Including a legacy in your Will, or adding a Codicil is a simple matter, although we do strongly advise that you take professional legal advice.</p>
<p><img alt="Legacy brochure" src="https://www.alumniweb.ox.ac.uk/new/view.image?Id=5511" /></p>
<p><a href="http://www.new.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/Alumni/form1%20-%20what%20form%20of%20legacy%20is%20right%20for%20you.pdf">What form of legacy is right for you?</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.new.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/Alumni/form2%20-%20legacy%20pledge%20form.pdf">Legacy pledge form</a></p>
<p><a href="http://www.new.ox.ac.uk/sites/default/files/Alumni/Form%203%20-%20reducing%20your%20inheritance%20tax%20bill%20by%20leaving.pdf">Reducing your inheritance tax bill by leaving a legacy to New College</a></p>
<p>If you choose to remember the College in your Will, do please let us know so that we can ensure that all aspects of your plans are fully understood and so that we can thank you appropriately. This will not represent a binding commitment, and your plans will be treated in the strictest confidence.</p>
<p>For Old Members in the United States, New College is part of a consortium with a number of Oxford colleges to facilitate methods of <a href="http://www.oxford.planyourlegacy.org/">Planned Gifts</a>. Specialists in Planned Giving services will provide advice on ways to support New College while taking advantage of favourable federal and state tax laws.</p>
<h2>&#160;</h2>
<h2>The Wykeham Society</h2>
<p>The Wykeham Society exists to thank everyone we know of who has helped us or who intends to help us in their estate plans; to give us a way of keeping in touch with you, and a way of keeping you in touch with us. We hold an annual Wykeham Society celebration &#8211; whether lunch, a concert, or a dinner &#8211; to thank you and to share with you our plans for the College's future, and to hear your feedback.</p>
<h2>&#160;</h2>
<h2>Suggested Wording for your Will</h2>
<h3>A Pecuniary Gift</h3>
<p>I give the sum of &#163; _____________ (in figures and words) to the New College Development Fund (Registered Charity No. 900202). I direct that the receipt of the Bursar for the time being of the College in his/her capacity as an ex-officio Trustee of the New College Development Fund, shall be a sufficient discharge to my executors.</p>
<h3>A Residuary Gift</h3>
<p>I give the whole (or a _______________ share)* of the residue of my estate to the New College Development Fund (Registered Charity No. 900202). I direct that the receipt of the Bursar for the time being of the College in his/her capacity as an ex-officio Trustee of the New College Development Fund, shall be a sufficient discharge to my executors.</p>
<h3>In the USA</h3>
<p>"I give (_____ dollars) (_____ percent) (all of the residue of my estate) to the Trustees of the American Friends of New College, Ltd, a 501(c)(3) charity, for the benefit of New College, Oxford, England (IF the bequest is for a specific purpose, state the purpose, "although I understand that this request is not binding on the part of the Trustees")."</p>
</section>
